;; Example questions file for parallel-research.sh
;; Copy to questions.edn and customize

{:adapton.rust
 {:path "~/Projects/best/adapton.rust/src"
  :question "How does Adapton handle incremental computation and derived values?
Focus on:
1) How it tracks dependencies between derived values
2) How it invalidates and recomputes when inputs change
3) What patterns it uses for memoization and caching
4) How it handles cycles
Be specific about the architecture and show code patterns."}

 :datascript
 {:path "~/Projects/best/datascript/src"
  :question "How does DataScript implement derived indexes and maintain them during transactions?
Focus on:
1) EAVT/AEVT/AVET index structure
2) How indexes are updated atomically
3) Efficient lookup patterns
4) Batch update strategies
Show concrete implementation patterns."}

 :clojurescript-compiler
 {:path "~/Projects/best/clojurescript/src/main/clojure/cljs"
  :question "How does ClojureScript compile high-level forms into lower-level representations?
Focus on:
1) The multi-pass compilation pipeline
2) How it normalizes/validates forms
3) The intermediate representation (AST)
4) Error accumulation patterns
Show the pipeline architecture."}

 :electric
 {:path "~/Projects/best/electric/src/hyperfiddle/electric"
  :question "How does Electric Clojure handle reactive derived state and propagation?
Focus on:
1) How it tracks dependencies between reactive values
2) How it propagates changes efficiently
3) Patterns for avoiding recomputation
4) How it handles cycles
Show the core architecture."}

 :integrant
 {:path "~/Projects/best/integrant/src"
  :question "How does Integrant implement its extension and dependency resolution system?
Focus on:
1) How it resolves dependencies topologically
2) How multimethods enable extension
3) The initialization/halting lifecycle
4) Composability patterns
Show implementation examples."}

 :re-frame
 {:path "~/Projects/best/re-frame/src/re_frame"
  :question "How does re-frame implement its interceptor pipeline and event normalization?
Focus on:
1) The interceptor chain architecture
2) How it composes and sequences transformations
3) How it handles errors in the pipeline
4) How coeffects and effects work
Show the threading patterns."}
}
